WEBVTT

1.1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.086
C R M and lead vocabulary — the shared language of BD, Sales, and Management.

1.2
00:00:06.086 --> 00:00:12.172
This module has a structure ready, and a source on the way.

2.1
00:00:12.172 --> 00:00:17.557
Why does this module exist?

2.2
00:00:17.557 --> 00:00:22.943
Because the same words must mean the same thing to everyone.

2.3
00:00:22.943 --> 00:00:28.328
When BD, Sales, and Management write identical C R M notes, a lead never gets lost in translation.

3.1
00:00:28.328 --> 00:00:34.407
Here is what this module will cover once its source lands.

3.2
00:00:34.407 --> 00:00:40.486
The canonical list of lead statuses and what each one means.

3.3
00:00:40.486 --> 00:00:46.565
Lead types and opportunity stages.

3.4
00:00:46.565 --> 00:00:52.644
The shared vocabulary Sales must recognise — D R F, Closure Form, Principally Agreed, B O Q — even where Design or Factory own the work.

4.1
00:00:52.644 --> 00:00:59.317
And the honest part: the content itself comes from two Notion pages — the C R M funnel taxonomy and the glossary — that have not been pasted yet.

4.2
00:00:59.317 --> 00:01:05.991
Nothing here is invented.

4.3
00:01:05.991 --> 00:01:12.664
The module, and its flashcard quiz, unlock the moment the source text arrives.

5.1
00:01:12.664 --> 00:01:18.419
Until then, note three things.

5.2
00:01:18.419 --> 00:01:24.174
One — this module is structure-ready, waiting only on its source.

5.3
00:01:24.174 --> 00:01:29.929
Two — the vocabulary to watch for: D R F, Closure Form, Principally Agreed, B O Q.

5.4
00:01:29.929 --> 00:01:35.684
Three — the goal: the same words meaning the same thing to BD, Sales, and Management.

6.1
00:01:35.684 --> 00:01:39.490
Module nine is on deck.

6.2
00:01:39.490 --> 00:01:43.296
Watch this space — the vocabulary lands with the source.

